<b>-----Text Settings-----</b>


<b>Text Format  </b>
<b>---------------------------------------</b>

<b>Chars Per inch  </b>
Prints the document by characters per inch. For example, if you want to print the characters inches per inch, click chars per inch box.

<b>Lines Per Inch  </b>
Prints the lines of the document by lines per inch.

<b>Number of Columns </b>
You can print the document in 'n' columns on a single page. Give the number of columns here.

<b>Syntax Color</b>
You can turn the syntax color on/off to set the syntax coloring on/off. You can customise the syntax coloring according to type of document like C-source, perl source etc. To use this you should have exported the environment variable CONTENT_TYPE to the following values : 
application/x-cshell
application/x-csource
application/x-perl
application/x-shell

<b>Wrap Text Lines</b>
Manages text wrapping. Lines will be wrapped if selected, or truncated otherwise.
